author: gawor
msg: optimizations: just create the common serializers/deserializer factories directly, no need for reflection

author: gawor
msg: fixed resource issues (tests were failing), optimized StringUtils.strip() to do substring ones

author: tomj
msg: Map serializer fix: Map keys and values can be any type, so should always
send xsi:type information on those elements.
Also, get the current encoding from the message context so we do not
emit a soapenc prefix when using literal serialization.

author: tomj
msg: Fix a problem with WSDD type mappings.  If you registered the same QName
in both encoded and literal, encoding styles the last one "wins",
Keep the data structure a Map to prevent the list from growing when a service
is redeployed, but include the encodingStyle in the Key.
